export const ART_RECIPE_VERSION = 'v30';  // STONE-LOWER-HALF WATERMILL + SUBMERGED WHEEL: a wet mill is built STONE up to the wheel storey (the load-bearing, splash-battered lower half) with a timber loft over it ÔÇö so the `watermill` preset is now a 2-storey body carrying a FULL-STOREY (1.35-tile) stone `baseCourse` (stone ground floor / undercroft, tar-timber loft) instead of a single timber storey, and its waterwheel gains a `submerge` param (`structural.ts` waterwheel: `cz = radius Ôłĺ submerge`, default 0.1, preset 0.38) so the wheel's lower arc DIPS below the ground/waterline into the millrace instead of resting on it. Compose OUTPUT changes for the watermill only; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box) hold. (v29 ÔÇö WATERMILL WATERWHEEL + SACRED-SPIRE PROPORTIONING: the watermill gains its defining silhouette ÔÇö a big vertical WATERWHEEL (new `waterwheel` composite prim/`solidWaterwheel`: twin annulus rims + radial spokes + hub + axle + circumferential paddle boards, one unioned timber solid; new `waterwheelPartType` mounts it OUTSIDE a chosen wall face, dipping to ~ground/water). The sacred spire is now SIZED to the building it crowns instead of a fixed `width:1.5`: a long nave carries a grounded broach WEST TOWER, but a short cell (a 2├Ś2 wayside shrine) gets a slender ridge FL├łCHE ÔÇö no fat tower swallowing the footprint (`solids.ts` spire vent). Buttresses are gated to a real masonry SPAN (footprint Ôëą4 tiles) so a tiny shrine no longer wears chunky corner piers (`body.ts`). Compose OUTPUT changes for the watermill (new wheel) + any small worship building with a spire/buttresses (shrine, church-axial cells) Ôçĺ version bump; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box) hold. (v28 ÔÇö PARISH-CHURCH SPIRE = PYRAMID (broach), not a cone: a new `pyramid` prim (`solids.ts` `solidPyramid` ÔÇö a true 4-sided taper over an axis-aligned footprint) replaces the round cone cap on SQUARE towers + the sacred spire vent, so the four wall corners no longer poke up 